Title: 'Only in South Africa '
DateModified: '2019-02-11'
DatePublished: '2019-02-11'
Url: https://www.worldnomads.com/create/scholarships/writing/2019/applications/only-in-south-africa
SetInCountry: South Africa
Category: A leap into the unknown
AuthorName: Nonjabulo  Lekhethoa
AuthorCountry: South Africa
Text: "I\u2019m a South African and believe me,I don\u2019t know my whole country,\
  \ I consider myself a traveler at heart but how am I a traveler if I don\u2019t\
  \ know my own country??\n\nA couple of years ago my friends and I decided to embark\
  \ on journey to Cape Town as a girl\u2019s getaway. It was our 21st birthday and\
  \ we were so excited about the whole trip. This was my first trip with friends and\
  \ my first time on a plane. It felt like taking a leap into the unknown; I was scared\
  \ and excited at the same time about being on a plane, Taking a trip with just my\
  \ two friends with no parents. It was exciting and scary at the same time. Spending\
  \ a whole week in Cape Town felt like being in another country, it\u2019s didn\u2019\
  t feel like the busy joburg that I\u2019m from; it actually didn\u2019t feel like\
  \ I was in South Africa. Being on a boat to the Robben Island felt like going to\
  \ another far away country; all I expected was a piece of land with Nelson Mandela\u2019\
  s jail cell. But when we landed we were met by a colony of penguins; how I love\
  \ these birds. It felt so rejuvenating seeing them face to face,I only saw them\
  \ on tv. It really didn\u2019t feel like a leap into the unknown because we didn\u2019\
  t plan anything,no set itinerary,we just went with our guy feeling..."
